        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 13 at 2:09PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 208 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Harkeyville, or near Algerita, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
San Saba, Algerita, Cherokee, Colorado Bend State Park, Chappel,
Sloan, Harkeyville, Locker, and Spring Creek.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
